    "created_at": "2014-11-18T17:45:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-11-18T17:45:56Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm reluctant to expose this as a piece of API that people can replace like this, because I think we will want to change the interface for the next release (e.g. to do exactly this kind of thing officially) without feeling bound by maintaining API compatibility for people using custom KernelSpecManagers.\n\nFor now, I would recommend that people do this by using the hooks virtualenvwrapper exposes to automatically create a corresponding kernel spec when you create a venv, rather than making IPython aware of your virtualenvs.\n"
  },
